{{Quote|Threepio, I hope you know Gamorrean.''"<br />"''Oh, dear|[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and [[C-3PO/Legends|C-3PO]]|<ref name="Children of the Jedi (novel)">[[Children of the Jedi (novel)|''Children of the Jedi'']]</ref>}}
'''Gamorrese''', or the '''Gamorrean language,''' was the native language of the [[Gamorrean/Legends|Gamorrean]] species, who lived on their [[Homeworld/Legends|homeworld]] of [[Gamorr/Legends|Gamorr]] and colonies such as [[Pzob/Legends|Pzob]].

Gamorrese was just a bunch of lexicon, mainly nouns and verbs plus a few adjectives, with a primitive syntax. Although apparently there were no declensions in Gamorrean, it was unclear if the word order provided the meaning of the sentences.

Gamorreans used Gamorrean words as their names, so that the meaning of a Gamorrean name is, more or less, some kind of threat. Other Gamorreans could be
intimidated if they hear "I am [[Ortugg]]," or "I'm going to ''Ortugg'' you".

Although Gamorrese did not have a sophisticated written language it did have a very basic runic alphabet which was used for record keeping, accounting and genealogy. The runic alphabet was only typically used by educated sows although a fair number of boars could read them slowly. There were known to be several variations of the runic alphabet. Since Gamorreans encountered in the galaxy were mostly males it was generally considered that the Gamorreans had no written language.

There was no word for "calculus" in Gamorrese. The closest expression translated as "big nasty math".<ref name="XWMC">''[[X-Wing: Mercy Kill]]''</ref>

One of the Gamorrean dialects was called [[Vregg]].

The blue and gold [[Protocol droid/Legends|protocol droid]] [[N2-3P0|N2-3PO]] peppered her speech with Gamorrean curses.

[[Journalist/Legends|Journalist]] [[Kandra Nilitz]] was able to understand Gamorrese<ref name="Fate of the Jedi: Conviction">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Conviction]]''</ref> and so was [[Myri Antilles]].<ref name="XWMC" />

==Glossary of terms==
[[File:Gamorrean_Runes.jpg|thumb|200px|Gamorrean Runes]]
*[[Arg'garok/Legends|''arg'garok'']] - Gamorrean axe
*''dinn'' - adjective, ("inclined to drool excessively")
*''gnorn'' ("Cowardice" - closest word to "Cunning" and "knowledge")
*''gweek'' - adjective, ("strong")
*''muh'' - ("Outlander", not native to [[Gamorr/Legends|Gamorr]])
*''[[m'uhk'gfa]]'' - Gamorrean battle armor
*''oink'' - a deadly insult that might start a war
*''scabwit'' - a derisive term
*''[[thogk]]'' - Traditional Gamorrean club ("log with a spike in it")
*''urrjsh'' or ''urrsh'' - command, ("stop")
*''v'lch'' - ("unmarried sow") - often used derogatorily
*gurk - big nasty math

==Behind the scenes==
Gamorrese first appeared, albeit unidentified, in [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']].<ref name="ROTJ">{{Film|VI}}</ref> It was later given text in ''[[X-Wing: The Krytos Trap]]''.<ref name="Krytos">''[[X-Wing: The Krytos Trap]]''</ref> The [[2003]] sourcebook ''[[Ultimate Alien Anthology]]'' stated that the language had no written form,<ref name="Ultimate">''[[Ultimate Alien Anthology]]''</ref> in contradiction to the [[1997]] short story "[[Murder in Slushtime]]," in which Gamorrean runes were pictued.<ref name="Murder">{{JournalCite|14|Murder in Slushtime}}</ref>

